# Shopify Deploy Safety

This repo is a live Shopify production theme. When pushing to Shopify, ONLY push files that belong to the new landing pages we are building. Never push unrelated files.

## Allowed files for push

Only the following files may be pushed to Shopify:

### Templates
- `templates/index.home-v2.json`

### Sections (new landing page sections only)
- `sections/Index-banner-slider-new.liquid`
- `sections/Index-bestsellers-cards-new.liquid`
- `sections/Index-collection-cards-new.liquid`
- `sections/Index-community-instagram-new.liquid`
- `sections/Index-comparison-new.liquid`
- `sections/Index-press-cards-new.liquid`
- `sections/Index-promise-product-new.liquid`
- `sections/Index-reviews-ugc-new.liquid`
- `sections/Index-technology-cta-new.liquid`

### Assets (CSS for new sections only)
- `assets/index-banner-slider-new.css`
- `assets/index-bestsellers-cards-new.css`
- `assets/index-collection-cards-new.css`
- `assets/index-community-instagram-new.css`
- `assets/index-comparison-new.css`
- `assets/index-press-cards-new.css`
- `assets/index-promise-product-new.css`
- `assets/index-reviews-ugc-new.css`
- `assets/index-technology-cta-new.css`

## Rules

1. **NEVER modify or push** `templates/index.json` -- this is the live A/B test control
2. **NEVER modify or push** existing sections, snippets, assets, layout, or config files
3. **NEVER modify** `layout/theme.liquid`, `config/settings_data.json`, or any other shared theme files
4. When adding new landing page sections or assets in the future, add them to the allowed list above
5. If a Shopify CLI command would push the entire theme, use `--only` flags to limit to allowed files
6. Always verify the push scope before executing any deploy command

## Push command pattern

```bash
# Push only specific landing page files
shopify theme push --only templates/index.home-v2.json --only sections/Index-banner-slider-new.liquid --only assets/index-banner-slider-new.css [... etc]
```
